<h2 style="margin-top: 30px" class="eleg">Gas Consumption and Emissions</h2>
<p>A car with a fuel efficiency of <input type="number" step="0.1" value="24.9" style="width:50px; padding: 4px" id="umpg" /> <abbr title="Miles per gallon">MPG</abbr> will need <strong id="gasgallons">1.62</strong> gallons of gas to cover the route between <strong>Stamford, CT</strong> and <strong>New York, NY</strong>.</p>
<p>The <strong>estimated cost</strong> of gas to go from Stamford to New York is <strong id="gascost">$5.39</strong>.</p>
<p>During the route, an average car will release <strong id="co2">31.65</strong> pounds of <strong>CO<sub>2</sub> to the atmosphere</strong>. The carbon footprint would be <strong id="co2footprint">0.79</strong> pounds of CO<sub>2</sub> per mile.</p>
<ul style="padding: 10px 0 0 20px; border-top: 1px solid #fff; margin: 0; font-size: 12px; color: #666">
<li>Average USA gas price used for calculation is $3.33 per gallon of regular gas. Price last updated on April 28, 2024.</li>
<li>Read more <a href="/about-co2-calculation">about our CO<sub>2</sub> calculation</a>.</li>
</ul>
